    "text_1": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Sneakerheads and golfers alike have been eagerly awaiting Nike's latest footwear drop for the 2024 US Open. This year, Nike's athletes, including Rory McIlroy, Brooks Koepka, and Tom Kim, will grace the greens of Pinehurst No. 2 in a series of stylish and high-performance golf shoes. Nike has unveiled three new limited-edition models: the Air Zoom Victory Tour 3 NRG, Air Pegasus '89 G NRG, and Air Zoom Infinity Tour NRG. Each shoe is designed to pay homage to Pinehurst No. 2 and North Carolina, featuring plenty of Carolina Blue. Let's dive into the details of each model and what makes them stand out.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": ["text_1"],
